    <h2>reading list</h2>

  
      <p><b>Week 2: Formal basics </b>
      <ul>
	<li> von Fintel, K. & I. Heim. 2011.  <a href="http://web.mit.edu/fintel/fintel-heim-intensional.pdf">Intensional semantics: lecture notes.</a>  Ms, MIT. [Chapters 1-2]</li> <br>
	<li> Kaufmann, S., C. Condoravdi & V. Harizanov.  2006.  <a href="modality20/Kaufmannetal06.pdf">Formal approaches to modality.</a>  In <i>The Expression of Modality</i>, W. Frawley (ed.).  Berlin: De Gruyter.</li>
	<br>

      </ul></p><br>
	<p><b>Week 3: Premise semantics (overview)</b>
	  <ul>
	    <li> Portner, P. 2009. <i>Modality.</i> Oxford: Blackwell.  [Chapters 1-2]</li><br>
	    <li> von Fintel, K. & I. Heim. 2011.  <a href="http://web.mit.edu/fintel/fintel-heim-intensional.pdf">Intensional semantics: lecture notes.</a>.  Ms, MIT. [Chapter 3]</li>
	    <br></ul></p><br>

	    <p><b>Week 4: Premise semantics</b>
	      <ul>
		<li> Lewis, D. 1975.  <a href="modality20/Lewis75.pdf">Adverbs of quantification.</a>  In <i>Formal Semantics: The Essential Readings,</i> P. Portner & B. Partee (eds.)</li><br>
		<li> Kratzer, A. 1981.  <a href="modality20/Kratzer81.pdf">The notional category of modality.</a>  In <i>Words, Worlds, and Contexts: New approaches to word semantics,</i> H.-J. Eikmeyer & H. Rieser (eds.), 38-74.  Berlin: De Gruyter.</li><br>
		<li> Kratzer, A. 1991. <a href="modality20/Kratzer91.pdf">Modality.</a>  In <i>Semantics: An International Handbook of Contemporary Research<i>, A. von Stechow & D. Wunderlich (eds.), 639-650. Berlin: De Gruyter.</li><br>
	      </ul>
	      </p><br>
		
